avy (R) scores a goal on a header past Costa Rican defenders during the World Cup second round soccer match between England and Cameroon 23 June 1990 in Bari. Skuhravy scored three goals as Czechoslovakia defeated Costa Rica 4-1.</p></DataContent></ContentItem></NewsComponent><NewsComponent><Role FormalName="Main" /><ContentItem Href="images/main/1990-crica-checos.jpg"><MediaType FormalName="Photo" /><Characteristics><Property FormalName="Width" Value="2048" /><Property FormalName="Height" Value="1546" /></Characteristics></ContentItem></NewsComponent><NewsComponent><Role FormalName="Thumbnail" /><ContentItem Href="images/thumbnail/1990-crica-checos.jpg"><MediaType FormalName="Photo" /><Characteristics><Property FormalName="Width" Value="150" /><Property FormalName="Height" Value="112" /></Characteristics></ContentItem></NewsComponent><NewsComponent><Role FormalName="Visu" /><ContentItem Href="images/visu/1990-crica-checos.jpg"><MediaType FormalName="Photo" /><Characteristics><Property FormalName="Width" Value="512" /><Property FormalName="Height" Value="386" /></Characteristics></ContentItem></NewsComponent></NewsComponent><NewsComponent Duid="photo5"><AdministrativeMetadata><Provider><Party FormalName="AFP" /></Provider><Creator><Party FormalName="DANIEL GARCIA" /></Creator></AdministrativeMetadata><NewsComponent><Role FormalName="Caption" /><ContentItem><MediaType FormalName="Text" /><Format FormalName="bcNITF2.5" /><DataContent><p>Italian forward Salvatore Schillaci (R) scores his team's first goal on a header past Czech goalkeeper Jan Stejsk during the World Cup first round soccer match between Italy and Czechoslovakia 19 June 1990 in Rome. Italy won 2-0.  AFP PHOTO/DANIEL GARCIA</p></DataContent></ContentItem></NewsComponent><NewsComponent><Role FormalName="Main" /><ContentItem Href="images/main/1990-schillaci-cze-but.jpg"><MediaType FormalName="Photo" /><Characteristics><Property FormalName="Width" Value="2048" /><Property FormalName="Height" Value="1808" /></Characteristics></ContentItem></NewsComponent><NewsComponent><Role FormalName="Thumbnail" /><ContentItem Href="images/thumbnail/1990-schillaci-cze-but.jpg"><MediaType FormalName="Photo" /><Characteristics><Property FormalName="Width" Value="140" /><Property FormalName="Height" Value="123" /></Characteristics></ContentItem></NewsComponent><NewsComponent><Role FormalName="Visu" /><ContentItem Href="images/visu/1990-schillaci-cze-but.jpg"><MediaType FormalName="Photo" /><Characteristics><Property FormalName="Width" Value="512" /><Property FormalName="Height" Value="452" /></Characteristics></ContentItem></NewsComponent></NewsComponent><NewsComponent Duid="photo6"><AdministrativeMetadata><Provider><Party FormalName="AFP" /></Provider><Creator><Party FormalName="PASCAL GEORGE" /></Creator></AdministrativeMetadata><NewsComponent><Role FormalName="Caption" /><ContentItem><MediaType FormalName="Text" /><Format FormalName="bcNITF2.5" /><DataContent><p>Argentinian goalkeeper Sergio Goycochea celebrates after stopping the penalty kick of Italian Roberto Donadoni (on ground) during the penalty shootout of the World Cup semifinal soccer match between Argentina and Italy 03 July 1990 in Naples. Argentina advanced to the final with a 4-3 victory on penalty kicks after the two teams were tied at 1 at the end of extra time. AFP PHOTO/PASCAL GEORGE</p></DataContent></ContentItem></NewsComponent><NewsComponent><Role FormalName="Main" /><ContentItem Href="images/main/1990-goycochea-ita2.jpg"><MediaType FormalName="Photo" /><Characteristics><Property FormalName="Width" Value="2048" /><Property FormalName="Height" Value="1405" /></Characteristics></ContentItem></NewsComponent><NewsComponent><Role FormalName="Thumbnail" /><ContentItem Href="images/thumbnail/1990-goycochea-ita2.jpg"><MediaType FormalName="Photo" /><Characteristics><Property FormalName="Width" Value="150" /><Property FormalName="Height" Value="102" /></Characteristics></ContentItem></NewsComponent><NewsComponent><Role FormalName="Visu" /><ContentItem Href="images/visu/1990-goycochea-ita2.jpg"><MediaType FormalName="Photo" /><Characteristics><Property FormalName="Width" Value="512" /><Property FormalName="Height" Value="351" /></Characteristics></ContentItem></NewsComponent></NewsComponent><NewsComponent Duid="photo7"><AdministrativeMetadata><Provider><Party FormalName="AFP" /></Provider><Creator><Party FormalName="GEORGES GOBET" /></Creator></AdministrativeMetadata><NewsComponent><Role FormalName="Caption" /><ContentItem><MediaType FormalName="Text" /><Format FormalName="bcNITF2.5" /><DataContent><p>West German defender Andreas Brehme (L) celebrates in front of forward Juergen Klinsmann after scoring the winning goal on a penalty kick  during the World Cup final between West Germany and Argentina 08 July 1990 in Rome. West Germany earned its third World title, after 1954 and 1974, beating the defending champions 1-0.  AFP PHOTO/GEORGES GOBET</p></DataContent></ContentItem></NewsComponent><NewsComponent><Role FormalName="Main" /><ContentItem Href="images/main/1990-brehme-arg-joie.jpg"><MediaType FormalName="Photo" /><Characteristics><Property FormalName="Width" Value="1698" /><Property FormalName="Height" Value="2048" /></Characteristics></ContentItem></NewsComponent><NewsComponent><Role FormalName="Thumbnail" /><ContentItem Href="images/thumbnail/1990-brehme-arg-joie.jpg"><MediaType FormalName="Photo" /><Characteristics><Property FormalName="Width" Value="119" /><Property FormalName="Height" Value="145" /></Characteristics></ContentItem></NewsComponent><NewsComponent><Role FormalName="Visu" /><ContentItem Href="images/visu/1990-brehme-arg-joie.jpg"><MediaType FormalName="Photo" /><Characteristics><Property FormalName="Width" Value="424" /><Property FormalName="Height" Value="512" /></Characteristics></ContentItem></NewsComponent></NewsComponent><NewsComponent Duid="photo8"><AdministrativeMetadata><Provider><Party FormalName="AFP " /></Provider></AdministrativeMetadata><NewsComponent>